Freescale i.MX233/i.MX28 USB loader
===================================

This tool allows user to load U-Boot via BootROM USB download.

Usage:
======
0) Apply patches (*.diff) onto kernel on your host machine, rebuild

1) Connect the MX233/MX28 device to USB via device cable

2) Apply this change to u-boot source code (still being investigated):

diff --git a/arch/arm/cpu/arm926ejs/mx28/start.S b/arch/arm/cpu/arm926ejs/mx28/start.S
index e572b78..5b5db8e 100644
--- a/arch/arm/cpu/arm926ejs/mx28/start.S
+++ b/arch/arm/cpu/arm926ejs/mx28/start.S
@@ -185,7 +185,7 @@ _reset:
         * not when booting from ram!
         */
 #ifndef CONFIG_SKIP_LOWLEVEL_INIT
-       bl      cpu_init_crit
+/*     bl      cpu_init_crit*/
 #endif
 
        bl      board_init_ll

3) Compile U-Boot, compile this tool

4) sudo ./mxsldr <path to u-boot.sb>
